trans-unit.source: The exception that is thrown when a SQL Server database is not enabled to support dependencies associated with the <see cref="T:System.Web.Caching.SqlCacheDependency" /> class.
The following code example is an exception handler for a simple administration page for setting up change notification in a SQL Server database.
trans-unit.target: 다음 코드 예제는 SQL Server 데이터베이스에 대 한 변경 알림을 설정에 대 한 간단한 관리 페이지에 대 한 예외 처리기입니다.

trans-unit.source: For the full code required to run the example, see the Example section of the <xref:System.Web.Caching.SqlCacheDependencyAdmin> class overview topic.
trans-unit.target: 예제를 실행 하는 데 필요한 전체 코드의 예 섹션을 참조 하십시오.는 <xref:System.Web.Caching.SqlCacheDependencyAdmin> 클래스 개요 항목입니다.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException" /> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException" /> class.

The <xref:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException.%23ctor%2A> creates a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException> class with all fields set to their default values.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException.%23ctor%2A> 의 새 인스턴스를 만듭니다는 <xref:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException> 을 해당 기본값으로 설정 된 모든 필드를 사용 하 여 클래스입니다.

trans-unit.source: A string that describes the error.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException" /> class.
The error message that explains the reason for the exception.
The exception that is the cause of the current exception.
If the <c>innerException</c> parameter is not <see langword="null" />, the current exception is raised in a catch block that handles the inner exception.

Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.Caching.DatabaseNotEnabledForNotificationException" /> class with a specified error message and a reference to the inner exception that is the cause of this exception.
